HEADWORD: Cuscus
<hw>Cus"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The same word as
<er>Couscous</er>, fr. F. <ets>couscous</ets> couscous, Ar.
<ets>kuskus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A soft grass
(<spn>Pennisetum typhoideum</spn>) found in all tropical regions, used
as food for men and cattle in Central Africa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

